From e727919b97c4baeca93cb7700d4adf2e35a3530f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Moskalev <irker@irker.net>
Date: Thu, 26 Nov 2020 10:30:02 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] cURL: make possible to send file from buffer string

Add CURLStringFile class which works similarly to CURLFile, but
uploads a file from a string rather than a file. This avoids the
need to create a temporary file, or use of a data:// stream.

Basic usage:

    $file = new CURLStringFile($data, 'filename.txt', 'text/plain');
    curl_setopt($curl, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, ['file' => $file]);

Closes GH-6456.
